{{about|媒体词汇|非形式谬误|诉诸中庸|比较上的谬误|{{tsl|en|False equivalence|错误对等}}}}
[[File:False_balance.jpg|thumb]]

'''虚假平衡'''<ref>{{cite journal |author1=严俊 |title=从“气候门”事件看美国媒体的虚假平衡报道 |journal=《新闻记者》 |date=2010 |volume=7 |pages=64-68 |url=https://www.cnki.com.cn/Article/CJFDTotal-XWJZ201007021.htm |accessdate=2021-03-09}}</ref>（{{lang-en|false balance}}），或称'''两面主义'''（{{lang|en|bothsidesism}}），是一种新闻工作者的[[媒體偏見|媒體偏見]]；它指在證據所能支持的範圍外，平衡地展現兩種對立觀點。新闻工作者可能会在报道中为一个问题的争论双方列出与实际比例不符的证据，或者可能遗漏一方的信息造成该方的主张无根据。虚假平衡被学者认为是传播[[錯誤資訊|錯誤資訊]]的因素之一<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Boykoff|first1=Maxwell T|last2=Boykoff|first2=Jules M|title=Balance as bias: global warming and the US prestige press|journal=Global Environmental Change|volume=14|issue=2|pages=125–136|doi=10.1016/j.gloenvcha.2003.10.001|year=2004}}</ref>。

虚假平衡有时会源于类似[[轰动效应|轰动效应]]的动机，作者和编辑可能会觉得一篇被描绘成有争议的报道会比更准确地描述这个问题的报道更有商业价值。与许多其他媒体偏见不同，虚假平衡也可能起源于试图避免偏见；作者和编辑可能会对某一问题感到困惑，并将两种互相竞争的观点“平等”地比较。例如，即便在有一方观点是基于错误的前提下，媒体仍然因其具实际价值和显著性，从而比例平等地对待双方的观点，给予双方相同的篇幅<ref>{{cite news |url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=940CE6DB1E3FF933A05752C0A9609C8B63 |title=A False Balance |last=Krugman |first=Paul |author-link=保罗·克鲁格曼 |newspaper=[[纽约时报|The New York Times]] |date=2006-01-30 |accessdate=2021-03-09 |archive-date=2017-10-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171019223808/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=940CE6DB1E3FF933A05752C0A9609C8B63 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

{{tsl|en|Science journalism|科学新闻}}中有关虚假平衡的例子包括[[全球变暖|全球变暖]]与自然[[氣候變遷|氣候變遷]]的比较、{{tsl|en|health effects of tobacco|吸烟对健康的影响}}、[[硫柳汞和疫苗|硫柳汞疫苗与自闭症的关系]]<ref name="Gross">{{cite journal|author=Gross L|year=2009|title=A broken trust: lessons from the vaccine—autism wars|journal=[[PLoS_Biol|PLoS Biol]]|volume=7|issue=5|pages=756–9|doi=10.1371/journal.pbio.1000114|pmc=2682483|pmid=19478850}}</ref>、[[演化|演化]]与[[智能设计|智能设计]]等<ref>{{cite book|url=https://ncse.com/files/pub/evolution/EvC--Chapter2.pdf|title=Evolution vs. Creationism: An Introduction|last1=Scott|first1=Eugenie C.|date=2009|publisher=Greenwood Press|isbn=9780313344275|edition=Second|location=Westport, CT|access-date=2017-11-01|archive-date=2013-11-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131102090044/http://ncse.com/files/pub/evolution/EvC--Chapter2.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==例子==
===亚美尼亚种族灭绝===
{{main|亚美尼亚种族灭绝}}
{{tsl|en|Terrence Des Pres|特伦斯·德斯·普雷斯}}于1986年报道称“有关亚美尼亚种族灭绝的事实直到最近仍被认为不存在争议”。但在最近，一方面由于土耳其的地缘政治地位，另一方面由于人们越来越倾向于把每一个问题的正反双方当作同样合理来处理，亚美尼亚种族灭绝相关的事实变得越来越模糊<ref>{{cite journal|title=On Governing Narratives: The Turkish-Armenian Case|date=1986a|volume=LXXV|number=4|pp=517–531|first=Terrence |last=Des Pres|authorlink=Terrence Des Pres|journal=[[The_Yale_Review|The Yale Review]]|issn=0044-0124}}</ref>。

===全球变暖===
{{main|{{tsl|en|Media coverage of climate change|媒体对气候变化的报道}}}}
[[全球变暖|全球变暖]]问题上的辩论往往是虚假平衡的体现。尽管科学界几乎一致认为1950年以后的全球变暖是由[[第一次工业革命|第一次工业革命]]所导致<ref>{{cite book |editor1-last=Edenhofer |editor1-first=Ottmar |editor2-last=Pichs-Madruga |editor2-first=Ramón |editor3-last=Sokona |editor3-first=Youba |display-editors=etal |date=2014 |title=Climate Change 2014: Mitigation of Climate Change: Working Group III contribution to the Fifth Assessment Report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change |location=Cambridge, UK; New York |publisher=[[劍橋大學出版社|Cambridge University Press]] |isbn=9781107058217 |oclc=892580682 |doi=10.1017/CBO9781107415416 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JAFEBgAAQBAJ |access-date=2021-03-09 |archive-date=2020-08-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801133314/https://books.google.com/books?id=JAFEBgAAQBAJ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite book | publisher = [[National_Academies_Press|National Academies Press]] | isbn = 978-0-309-14588-6 | last = America's Climate Choices: Panel on Advancing the Science of Climate Change; National Research Council | title = Advancing the Science of Climate Change | location = Washington, D.C. | year = 2010 | url = http://www.nap.edu/catalog.php?record_id=12782 | access-date = 2021-03-09 | archive-date = 2014-05-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140529161102/http://www.nap.edu/catalog.php?record_id=12782 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1073/pnas.0906548107 | volume = 107 | issue = 8 | pages = 3382–7 | last1 = Unger | first1 = Nadine |author-link1=Nadine Unger |first2=Tami C. |last2=Bond |first3=James S. |last3=Wang |first4=Dorothy M. |last4=Koch |first5=Surabi |last5=Menon |first6=Drew T. |last6=Shindell |first7=Susanne |last7=Bauer | title = Attribution of climate forcing to economic sectors | journal = [[美国国家科学院院刊|Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America]] | date = 2010-02-23 |pmid=20133724 |pmc=2816198 | bibcode = 2010PNAS..107.3382U }}</ref><ref>{{Cite book | publisher = The National Academies Press | isbn = 0-309-10225-1 | last = Committee on Surface Temperature Reconstructions for the Last 2,000 Years, National Research Council | title = Surface Temperature Reconstructions for the Last 2,000 Years | location = Washington, D.C. | year = 2006 | url = http://www.nap.edu/catalog.php?record_id=11676 | access-date = 2021-03-09 | archive-date = 2007-04-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070428155410/http://www.nap.edu/catalog.php?record_id=11676 | dead-url = no }}</ref>，仍有极少数的科学家质疑这一结论<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1073/pnas.1003187107 | volume = 107 | issue = 27 | pages = 12107–9 | last1 = Anderegg | first1 = William R. L. |first2=James W. |last2=Prall |first3=Jacob |last3=Harold |first4=Stephen H. |last4=Schneider |author4-link=斯蒂芬·施奈德 | title = Expert credibility in climate change | journal = Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences | date = 2010-07-06 | pmid=20566872 | pmc=2901439 |bibcode = 2010PNAS..10712107A }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1126/science.1103618 | volume = 306 | issue = 5702 | pages = 1686 | last = Oreskes | first = Naomi |author-link=内奥米·奥雷斯克斯 | title = The Scientific Consensus on Climate Change | journal = Science | date = 2004-12-03 | pmid=15576594 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1029/2009EO030002 | volume = 90 | issue = 3 | pages = 22–23 | first1 = Peter T. | last1 = Doran | first2 = Maggie Kendall | last2 = Zimmerman | title = Examining the Scientific Consensus on Climate Change | journal = Eos | date = 2009-01-20 | url = http://www.ucsusa.org/sites/default/files/legacy/testfolder/aa-migration-to-be-deleted/assets-delete-me/documents-delete-me/ssi-delete-me/ssi/DoranEOS09.pdf | bibcode = 2009EOSTr..90...22D | access-date = 2021-03-09 | archive-date = 2019-09-25 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190925203854/https://www.ucsusa.org/sites/default/files/legacy/testfolder/aa-migration-to-be-deleted/assets-delete-me/documents-delete-me/ssi-delete-me/ssi/DoranEOS09.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref>。给予双方平等的声音会让人觉得科学界内针对全球变暖这一问题存在严重的分歧，然而事实上[[关于气候变化的科学观点|主流科学共识]]认为人为的全球变暖始终存在。

===麻腮风三联疫苗争议===
{{main|麻疹腮腺炎德國麻疹混合疫苗爭議}}
众多观察家批评大众媒体不应卷入这一争议，并称状况犹如“{{tsl|en|science by press conference|新闻发布会科学}}”<ref name=EMBOreports>{{cite journal | author = Moore Andrew | year = 2006 | title = Bad science in the headlines: Who takes responsibility when science is distorted in the mass media? | url = http://www.nature.com/embor/journal/v7/n12/full/7400862.html | journal = [[EMBO_Reports|EMBO Reports]] | volume = 7 | issue = 12 | pages = 1193–1196 | doi = 10.1038/sj.embor.7400862 | pmid = 17139292 | pmc = 1794697 | access-date = 2021-03-09 | archive-date = 2020-07-03 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200703140131/http://www.nature.com/embor/journal/v7/n12/full/7400862.html/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>，并认为媒体为{{tsl|en|Andrew Wakefield|安德鲁·韦克菲尔德}}提供了其不应有的可靠性。一篇由肖纳·希尔顿（Shona Hilton）、马克·佩蒂克鲁（Mark Petticrew）及凯特·亨特（Kate Hunt）发表于《{{tsl|en|BioMed Central|生物医学中心|生物医学中心公共健康}}》2007年3月的研究显示媒体对安德鲁·韦克菲尔德的报道“造成了人们对疫苗导致自闭症的印象增强，尽管有大量证据反对这一观点”（created the misleading impression that the evidence for the link with autism was as substantial as the evidence against）<ref name=hilton>{{cite journal |vauthors=Hilton S, Petticrew M, Hunt K| year = 2007 | title = Parents' champions vs. vested interests: Who do parents believe about MMR? A qualitative study | journal = [[BMC_Public_Health|BMC Public Health]] | volume = 7 | page = 42 | pmc=1851707 | pmid=17391507 | doi=10.1186/1471-2458-7-42}}</ref>。此前，发表在《[[英國醫學期刊|英國醫學期刊]]》及《医学通讯》的一系列论文得出“媒体的报道在韦克菲尔德的假说上误导了大众”的结论<ref name=Speers>{{cite journal |vauthors=Speers T, Justin L |title= Journalists and jabs: media coverage of the MMR vaccine |journal= Communication and Medicine |volume= 1 |issue= 2 |pages= 171–181 |doi= 10.1515/come.2004.1.2.171 |pmid= 16808699 |date=2004-09}}</ref><ref name=Jacson>{{cite journal | author = Jackson T | year = 2003 | title = MMR: more scrutiny, please | journal = [[英國醫學期刊|The BMJ]] | volume = 326 | issue = 7401| page = 1272 | doi=10.1136/bmj.326.7401.1272| pmc = 1126154 }}</ref><ref name=Dobson>{{cite journal | author = Dobson Roger |date=2003-05 | title = Media misled the public over the MMR vaccine, study says | journal = The BMJ | volume = 326 | issue = 7399| page = 1107 | doi = 10.1136/bmj.326.7399.1107-a | pmc=1150987 | pmid=12763972}}</ref>。

